lexUnit.name: rustle.v
lexUnit.definition: COD: make a soft, muffled crackling sound like that caused by the movement of dry leaves or paper.

sentence.text: There it was -- complete with the taffeta underskirt that had once ( once only ) rustled so satisfyingly .
The cream lace of her dress rustled softly as she moved towards him , the pearl and diamond earrings he had bought her gleaming against the dark honey tone of her neck .
